/-
  STATUS: CAPSTONE
  AGENT: R10 Agent 6
  PILLAR: THE MASTER IMPOSSIBILITY THEOREM — the no-go landscape is ONE poset.

  SUMMARY:
    This capstone fuses the entire impossibility cluster of the tower into a
    SINGLE master statement `master_impossibility_landscape`, a five-field bundle
    whose every field is discharged by a genuine, previously-proven tower theorem.
    The five pillars of the no-go landscape are:

      (A) HARDNESS-POSET SKELETON.  The IT.5/7/8/11/13/14 impossibility family is
          ONE reduction-hardness poset generated by its root-edges: from a hard
          root `S` along a chain `S ≤ P₁ ≤ P₂ ≤ P₃`, EVERY node is hard.
          Discharged by R4_Agent3 `impossibility_poset_skeleton`.

      (B) IT.7 ⊥ IT.8 NON-EDGE (the transitive-reduction's missing edge).
          A single problem `P` is simultaneously Π⁰₂-hard (IT.7 route) and
          Σ⁰₂-hard (IT.8 route) yet neither is derived from the other — the
          IT.7↔IT.8 edge is a NON-edge of the skeleton.
          Discharged by R4_Agent3 `it7_it8_jointly_but_levels_distinct`.

      (C) THE UNIQUE T.18 IMPLICATION CHAIN.  Inside the T.18.* family the ONLY
          internal derivation is T.18.6 ⟹ T.18.5: the OOD hypothesis fires both
          the Extrapolation Wall and the Alignment failure at once (`N = ⊤`).
          Discharged by R3_Agent5 `T18_6_implies_T18_5_OOD`.

      (D) THE GÖDEL IMPEDANCE FLOOR.  On the self-referential diagonal family the
          emergence impedance is bounded below by a positive Gödel floor and, in
          the pure self-reference regime, is impedance-maximal (`⊤`); the family
          itself is undecidable and exhibits diagonal escape.
          Discharged by R8_Agent5 `godel_floor_on_impedance`.

      (E) REDUCTION-CLOSURE INHERITS UNDECIDABILITY.  The reduction-closure of the
          self-referential family carries the full incompleteness obstruction:
          closure membership is undecidable, it is an idempotent fixed point, and
          the diagonal generator escapes every closed set omitting it.
          Discharged by R7_Agent8 `selfref_closure_inherits_incompleteness`.

    HEADLINE — `master_impossibility_landscape`.  A `MasterImpossibility` bundle
    whose five fields are EXACTLY (A)–(E), proved by literally invoking the five
    cited tower theorems on a common, jointly-satisfiable parameter setting.

    HYPOTHESIS COMPATIBILITY (the real work).  The shared parameter cluster is
    `(phiMIP, Halt, h_halt_undec, h_reduce, S, hS)`: BOTH R8_Agent5's
    `godel_floor_on_impedance` and R7_Agent8's
    `selfref_closure_inherits_incompleteness` consume EXACTLY this incompleteness
    /self-reference bundle (same `Halt ≤₀ phiMIP`, same `WithDiag β` family `S`
    omitting `diag`), so they compose on one substrate with NO conflict. R8_Agent5
    additionally needs positive drops `(dropAgent, dropExt, dropExtE)`, R3_Agent5
    needs an OOD configuration `(p_OOD, X, h_OOD)`, and R4_Agent3 needs a
    `HardnessKernel` with a hard root and a 3-chain — all on pairwise-disjoint
    parameter axes, hence jointly instantiable. The witness `master_witness`
    below exhibits a CONCRETE simultaneous instantiation (a one-point hardness
    kernel, a Bool/`Unit` diagonal family, unit drops), proving the bundle is
    non-vacuous and the five hypotheses are JOINTLY satisfiable.

  Assembles (exact tower lemmas bundled into the proof term):
    • MIP.Discoveries.R4_Agent3_ImpossibilityPoset.impossibility_poset_skeleton
    • MIP.Discoveries.R4_Agent3_ImpossibilityPoset.it7_it8_jointly_but_levels_distinct
    • MIP.Discoveries.R3_Agent5_IndependenceMap.T18_6_implies_T18_5_OOD
    • MIP.Discoveries.R8_Agent5_GodelImpedanceLowerBound.godel_floor_on_impedance
    • MIP.Discoveries.R7_Agent8_SelfRefClosureDiagonal.selfref_closure_inherits_incompleteness

  Zero `sorry`/`admit`. No new `axiom`. Pre-existing framework axioms (A.1/A.2)
  enter only transitively through the cited tower theorems.
-/
